column3: “This strain is awesome. A buddy of mine gifted me a few babies out of what he had and I was able to grow a few last year. It was an organic grow and I ended up with an average yield, but the smoke was great and after a week long cure was very, very smooth. It has an earthy, woody aroma and great flavor. Nice mellow (as in mood, not intensity) high. If I get it again I will probably keep a mother for personal and to s...”
“Your body feels stony and relaxed while your head is lifted into the land of smiles. Such a happy, fun, chill high. It's like reggae music in the summer. I may have to go back for more.”

“For me this was THE strain.  No side effects for me and great relief from stress.  I have an anxiety issue and their was NO anxiety or paranoia.  I know it may not be that way for everyone but dang this leaves me happy and smiling.”

“I'm a dabber the only way I'll smoke flower is if it's a free preroll. Surprisingly Wookies got me pretty toasted for a prerolls.
Helped time pass on my long bus ride back home after picking up my medicine in Phoenix 
Great for being social even if you normally have too much anxiety.
A solid 4 star strain.”
“Excellent high very uplifting”
“Beautifully relaxing high but still able to be sociable. Powerful indica type high but not overpowering so you can't function. Tasted incredible too! Minty fresh.”

“Wow!! Thee!! Prettiest bud 💨 ive ever seen not only that smokes amazingly smooth and smells like a cookie factory,the high seems to linger around much longer after consumption....😧😧 top notch fire ✊”

“Awesome smell: earthy & a bit piney with a menthol undertone. Very dense nuggets; opened one up and discovered a mine of shiny, sticky trichomes. Physical characteristics of Girl Scout Cookies (but with considerably different effects), and the frostiness of White 91 combine and birth Wookies, a smooth, pleasant flower mostly suitable for evenings (or really any other time than morning/afternoon). This one is worth tr...”

“My uncle is a complete raging alcoholic with an anger And he smokes a lot of different strains but none of them seem to calm him down on his anger today we rolled up a big fat joint and here we are writing a review on your app laughing our ass off he’s never been so happy in his life not even the day that he lost his virginity yesterday 41 to some random dispensary that we paid tons of cash thanks for the support gre...”
“This strain has a pine/earthy taste that gives you an upbeat high and is good for daytime use”

“I bought this in the shatter and made a vape pen out of it. It’s such a nice high! I have anxiety and get stoned quick. This got me feelin’ giggly and happy and surprisingly super creative. I personally wouldn’t feel comfortable going out or working after taking my pen hit only because it was so obvious with my smile and eyes that I was high. But for me, again someone with anxiety, I was super happy and felt creative...”

“Definitely a heavy hitter! 
After 2 bong hits [2 ft.] and 7 mins later, I was truely in lala land.  However, after about 40 minuets, Turned energetic, with a sativa feel.

Not for beginners, and also a creeper.

5 Stars for potency alone, and easy on the throat.”
“Super mellow”
“Favorite strain to cook with. The cookies have a great mint taste when using this bud. Not a bad smoke either.”

“Great looking long slim buds with a nice pungent smell and trychomes. A nice full sized bowl in my Arizer Q Vape lasted 6 sessions!!! I'm blown away of the cloudy bags that keep coming after every stir.”

“Got super excited about a regular bud. seen this brand new screen at the dispensary @$60 an 8th. Thought to myself hell yeah" don't get me wrong it's a decent Indica leaning hybrid but it definitely was not worth $60. It got me high
column4: took my pain away but there's definitely nothing exceptionable except the the look
column5: this has beautiful hues and huge fence buds.”"

column3: “Excellent and uplifting! It's even easy to engage with my professor or other students during lecture! It most definitely allows focused attn and concentration during studies :) (senior@UT; major of Urban Studies, minor of Architecture). Tricky to find the best strain during semesters, so this is definitely, for me at least, like the perfect green tea ^_^”
“Sometimes things suck... but who cares when you have Wookies to rescue you.  I love this total stress reliever as much as the mighty Chewbacca himself!”

“Great sativa high - found myself especially inspired to write / paint on this strain. My body was relaxed, almost like a bowl of noodles or something but still able to function. 
Might be a new favorite”
“Very excellent strain, taste, smell, smokes beautiful!! lovely high.”
“Good for tv time”
“Very tasty! Great for pain and relaxing muscles. The taste is so unique and delicious. Very high in terpenoids.”
“great taste. very mentholy. half a blunt im gud”

“Great indica dominate strain
  Perfect for sleep and anxiety without being too heavy on the body high.  very good for anxiety while still needing to function, somewhat lol”
“This is some of the best smoke ever, one bowl and it’s on to headphones and my iPhone and massive stress relief with major creativity and back pain relief as well. Not for inexperienced people 😎”
“Best strain ive smoked so far!!!”
“Tastes exactly like a dab😍”
“Pleasant taste. Very quick high then it linger down on you to a nice body high . Body high last for a pretty long time.”
“I really enjoyed this one! My fav”
“One puff straight headshot can’t chain smoke if u do prepare to feel drowsy asl till ur sober”
“one of my top 5 strains....”

column3: “wow now this rocks for sure!!!”

“This strain is absolutely prime shit. It’s beautiful, it tastes really good. Very minty and fresh. The high was super satisfying. It also lasted fairly long for me which I liked. This particular high is ideal for creativity. I felt content and my mood was light as well. I recommend this!”

“I've used this flower before night time, it helps me sleep with out back pain.”
“One of the best strains for a good night sleep. It gave me the couch lock and i felt veeeeeery relaxed. Loved it. If i get the chance to buy it again ill do it without question.”
“Excillent uplifting yet sedating feeling.”
“Very relaxing however mentally very uplifting and euphoric.”
“Tastes little weird and isn’t too fire”

“Really good strain with minty and pine aroma.
That will lift your spirit and give nice focus”
“Soooooo Flame fo yourself a favor and pick up this flavor!”

“I just took. .2 snap out of my shower head perc bong and this strain definitely taste amazing! It had this minty fresh vanilla cupcake like taste to it that is super pungent with a creamy and earthy undertone. This strain delivers a very relaxed euphoric high with a happy uplifting sativa high you feel on the forehead/temporal part of your head. Recommended for anytime of day”

“Kind of a letdown, honestly. It has a very strong skunky smell, with a bit of menthol. It came in a lot of mid-size dense nugs, they're different shades of green with brown trichomes all around. It made me cough a bit, but it was pretty smooth. It gave me a nice head buzz. But honestly,  it being labeled 28.60% THC and descending from Girl Scout Cookie, I was hoping for something better. Plus I just wasn't digging th...”
“That is not the genetics of wookie Leafly! It is Lavendar x Appalachia (which does have some chem dog). Amazing strain and parent of Granola Funk.”

“I like this strain.  Focused, cerebral high, great for relaxation and pain relief.   I purchased this strain after reading Leafly's description that gave it medical high marks as a treatment for insomnia.  Do not buy Wookies as an insomnia treatment,  as there are much better strains for this purpose.  This is a better strain for afternoon or early evening use.  I docked it one star, not because it is a bad strain, b...”
